/// Logging interface for Pumpkin plugins.
///
/// This interface provides logging capabilities to plugins for debugging
/// and monitoring purposes. Supports multiple log levels to control
/// the verbosity of output.
///
/// # Log Levels
///
/// - `trace`: Very detailed information, typically of interest only when diagnosing problems.
/// - `debug`: Detailed information useful during development.
/// - `info`: Confirmation that things are working as expected.
/// - `warn`: Indication that something unexpected happened, or may indicate a problem.
/// - `error`: An error occurred, preventing the current operation from completing.
interface logging {
    /// Log levels for controlling message verbosity.
    enum level {
        /// Very detailed diagnostic information.
        trace,
        /// Information useful for debugging.
        debug,
        /// General informational messages.
        info,
        /// Warning messages for unexpected conditions.
        warn,
        /// Error messages for failures.
        error,
    }

    /// Logs a message at the specified level.
    ///
    /// * `level`: The severity level of this message.
    /// * `message`: The text to log.
    log: func(level: level, message: string);

    /// Logs a tracing event.
    ///
    /// This function is meant to be used by the tracing crate
    /// for structured logging. The event is a serialized tracing event.
    log-tracing: func(event: list<u8>);
}
